<chapter version="5.0" xml:id="KIM_Type" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
    <title>KIM Type</title>
    
    <section>
        <title>KIM Type Lookup</title>
        
        <para>Use this lookup when you create a new group in KIM to find the KIM
            Type for the new group.</para>
        
        <figure>
            <title>KIM Type Lookup</title>
            
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/Kim_type_lookup_new.png" width="100%" scalefit="1"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
        
        <para>You may enter information in one or more of the search fields to
            find the correct Type for your new group:</para>
        
        <para><table frame="none" tabstyle="striped">
            <title>KIM Type Lookup Attributes</title>
            
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.5*"/>
                
                <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Field Name</entry>
                        
                        <entry>Description</entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Namespace Code</entry>
                        
                        <entry>Optional. Select the code of the application and module
                            for this KIM Type.</entry>
                    </row>
                    
                    <row>
                        <entry>Type Name</entry>
                        
                        <entry>Optional. Enter the name for this KIM Type.</entry>
                    </row>
                    
                    <row>
                        <entry>Type Identifier</entry>
                        
                        <entry>Optional. Enter the unique system-assigned Identifier
                            for this KIM Type.</entry>
                    </row>
                    
                    <row>
                        <entry>Active Indicator</entry>
                        
                        <entry>Required. Defaults to Yes (Yes means display only
                            Active Types). Change the default selection to view KIM Types
                            that are Inactive or Types that are both Active and
                            Inactive.</entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table></para>
        
        <figure>
            <title>KIM Type Lookup: Results Example</title>
            
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/kim_type_lookup_results_new.png" width="100%" scalefit="1"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
        
        <para>The search results list for this screen has the same fields as the
            <emphasis role="bold">Lookup</emphasis> screen. To select the Type you
            want to use for your new group, click the <emphasis role="bold">return
                value</emphasis> link for it in the search results list.</para>
    </section>
    
    <section>
        <title>KIM Type Inquiry</title>
        
        <para>The KIM Type Inquiry screen provides details about a KIM Type data
            element.</para>
        
        <para>To access this screen, from the <emphasis role="bold">Kim Type Lookup</emphasis>
            screen, click a <emphasis role="bold">Type Name</emphasis> in your search results
            list.</para>
        
        <figure>
            <title>KIM Type Inquiry</title>
            
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/kim_type_new.png" width="100%" scalefit="1"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
        
        <para>All fields are defined above in <emphasis role="italic">KIM Type
            Lookup</emphasis> except these:</para>
        
        <para><table frame="none" tabstyle="striped">
            <title>KIM Type Inquiry Attributes</title>
            
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.5*"/>
                
                <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Field Name</entry>
                        
                        <entry>Description</entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Service Name</entry>
                        
                        <entry>Display-only. The name of the service associated with
                            this KIM Type</entry>
                    </row>
                    
                    <row>
                        <entry>Namespace Code</entry>
                        
                        <entry>Display-only. The namespace code associated with the
                            selected KIM Type</entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table></para>
    </section>
</chapter>
